### User:
in javascript how do you save to and read back from localstorage

### Response:


To save data in LocalStorage, use the `localStorage.setItem()` method with a key and value parameter. To retrieve stored data, use the `localStorage.getItem()` method with a key parameter. For example:
```javascript
// Save data to local storage
localStorage.setItem("name", "John Doe");

// Retrieve saved data from local storage
var name = localStorage.getItem("name");
console.log(name); // Outputs "John Doe"
```
